Section Two
Chapter One
How to run Java program using CMD without IDE

1.Make sure you have the Java Development Kit (JDK) installed.
-To check, open CMD and type: java -version and java -version
2.Set Environment Variables (if needed)
-Ensure the bin folder of JDK is added to your PATH.
3.Write Your Java File
 - Create a file, e.g., HelloWorld.java:

 public class HelloWorld {
     public static void main(String[] args) {
         System.out.println("Hello, World!");
     }
 }
 4. Open CMD and Navigate to File Location
 - Use cd to change directory to where your file is saved:
 - cd C:\Users\YourName\Desktop
 5. Compile the Java File
 - Run:
   javac HelloWorld.java
 - This generates a HelloWorld.class file (the bytecode).
 6. Run the Compiled Class
 - Execute:
 - java HelloWorld
 - Output should be:
 Hello, World!


Flow Diagram
   ┌─────────────────────┐
   │   Write Code        │
   │   HelloWorld.java   │
   └─────────┬───────────┘
             │
             ▼
   ┌─────────────────────┐
   │   Compile Code       │
   │   javac HelloWorld.java
   └─────────┬───────────┘
             │
             ▼
   ┌─────────────────────┐
   │   Bytecode File      │
   │   HelloWorld.class   │
   └─────────┬───────────┘
             │
             ▼
   ┌─────────────────────┐
   │   Run Program        │
   │   java HelloWorld    │
   └─────────┬───────────┘
             │
             ▼
   ┌─────────────────────┐
   │   Output             │
   │   "Hello, World!"    │
   ─────────────────────┘

7. Difference between java and javac

java-version
Runs the Java Runtime Environment (JRE)
The version of the Java interpreter (the program that executes compiled .class bytecode)

javac-version
Runs the Java Compiler (part of JDK)
The version of the Java compiler (the program that converts .java source code into .class bytecode)

8.  .java
-Contains java source code
-High Level Human Readable
-Used for Development
-File is editable

9.   .class

-Contains java bytecode
-For consumption of JVM
-Used for execution
-Not meant to be edited

